<br>
You're gonna need:<br>
3 Hearts<br>
-1 planarian larvae<br>
-1 crystal spider<br>
-1 razorfiend<br>
<br>
3 Pieces of the Crystalline Globe<br>
-1 from the undead.  I got mine at the vassals camp.<br>
-1 from the Luminii Crawlers.<br>
-1 from the frogs near the bridgehouse area.<br>
<br>
Gather all this crap first, it'll save time later.  Once you have it, you start the quest by first hailing Johan Popoah(sp?) he's in the tents near the ZI.  You hail him twice, there's also some dialogue to run through there as well.  Basically, if he doesn't look like he's going to talk with you anymore, hail him again and see if you get more dialogue options.  <br>
<br>
JP sends you to his buddy Paralin Notion.  Same general area as before.  Run the dialogue with him for a bit.  Key words are:<br>
1. I am brave.  (no idea what I am stupid gets you).<br>
2. I will help our company.<br>
3. What squad?<br>
4. What about that razorfiend?<br>
5. I will provide you with assistance.<br>
6. What trials?  (I don't think this one is absolutely necessary, but you may as well ask).<br>
7. What things?<br>
<br>
PN sends you to see Master Sergeant Aramis Darlyn in the bridgehouse.<br>
1. I am here to aid the cause.<br>
2. Who is Aerin'dar?<br>
<br>
MSAD tells you to bugger off, so you go back to PN and hail him again.<br>
1. How shall I prove myself?<br>
&lt;Hand in the three hearts here&gt;<br>
PN sends you back to MSAD.<br>
<br>
MSAD is now much happier to talk with you when you hail him.<br>
1. What glass lair?<br>
2. What about Aerin'dar?<br>
3. What company?<br>
4. What mission?<br>
<br>
MSAD sends you to see Captain Ryglot Cupperhide.  Not sure where he's located, but I'd start in the bridgehouse area.<br>
1. Why are you busy?<br>
2. I will help.<br>
3. What mission?<br>
4. What war?<br>
5. I am willing to help.<br>
&lt;Hand in the three pieces of the crystalline globe now&gt;<br>
<br>
You should now have the key to Aerin'dar's Lair.  Remember to zone in to HoH as soon as you get the flag from defeating Aerin'dar, so you temporary flag from hailing the planar projection becomes permanent and you can use the PoT zonein instead of having to wall all the way back through the lair when you want to zone in.<br>
<br>
